While these vehicles are parked and do not present an immediate dynamic threat, caution is advised in case any of the vehicles begin to move or if a driver exits and becomes a pedestrian.

The image does not show any traffic lights that would influence the driving behavior of the ego car, indicating that there is no need for the vehicle to alter its behavior in response to traffic light signals.

Lastly, there are traffic cones or delineators that are positioned to demarcate the active driving lane from the parking area. These indicate the boundaries of the driving area, and the ego car should maintain a safe distance from these objects to avoid any potential damage to the vehicle or the cones.
